dc_title_s: PSAP Service Area Boundaries, Fire, EMS and Law Enforcement Districts Pepin County, WI 2020
dc_description_s: [All PSAP, Fire, EMS, & Law boundary data are embedded in same file]. Along with EMS, Fire and Law Enforcement districts -- this data layer represents 911 Public Safety Answering Point (PSAP) service area boundaries in Pepin county, Wisconsin in 2020. According to the National Emergency Number Association (NENA), a Public Safety Answering Point (PSAP) is a facility equipped and staffed to receive 9-1-1 calls. The service area is the geographic area within which a 911 call placed using a landline is answered at the associated PSAP.
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison.
